==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''fastus'': [[disdain]]. Perhaps from Sansrtit root ''bila'' [[splendid]] - hence ironic ''fastus''.

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æʃ|-æʃ]]

===Verb===
'''verb'''
# {{italbrac|Georide & Scottish}} To [[worry]]. e.g. ; to [[bother]].
#: ''"Divint '''fash''' yersel"'' = "don't worry"

===Noun===
'''fash'''
# {{italbrac|Georide & Scottish}} A [[worry]]; [[trouble]]; [[bother]].

